---
alwaysApply: true
---
- Implement JWT-based authentication with refresh token rotation.
- Store passwords using bcrypt with salt rounds >= 12.
- Use HTTP-only, Secure, SameSite cookies for token storage when possible.
- Implement rate limiting per IP and per user to prevent brute force attacks.
- Validate and sanitize all user inputs to prevent SQL injection and XSS.
- Implement CORS with explicit whitelist of allowed origins.
- Use HTTPS in production and enforce TLS 1.2+.
- Implement account lockout after failed login attempts (max 5 attempts, lock for 15 minutes).
- Implement proper authorization checks (RBAC or ACL) for protected routes.
- Never expose internal IDs; use UUIDs or opaque tokens for external references.
- Implement token blacklisting for logout and password change scenarios.
- Use short-lived access tokens (15 minutes) with refresh token rotation.
- Log security events (login attempts, password changes) for audit trails.
- Implement CSRF protection for state-changing operations.
- Validate file uploads with proper MIME type checking and size limits.
- Never trust client-side validation; always re-validate on server.
